From: LotusWorks <apinales@lotusworks.io>
Subject: [PATCH] tlv320adcx140: fix CH2 slot assignment for I2S and Left-Justified modes

In I2S (and Left-Justified) mode the FSYNC signal splits the frame into a
left half (FSYNC high) and a right half (FSYNC low).  The ADC determines
which physical BCLKs to drive based on which FSYNC half a slot falls in:
slots 0-31 are "left slots" (FSYNC-high period) and slots 32-63 are "right
slots" (FSYNC-low period).

The power-on-reset value for ASI_CH2 is 0x01 ("left slot 1"), which is
correct for TDM mode where slots are numbered sequentially from the FSYNC
edge regardless of polarity.  In I2S mode, however, "left slot 1" is the
second slot-width inside the FSYNC-high window.  For a standard stereo
frame (64 BCLKs, 32 per FSYNC half) only one slot fits in the FSYNC-high
period, so "left slot 1" extends past the FSYNC falling edge and the ADC
never drives the data line for it — producing hard zeros on the right
channel at the I2S wire level regardless of gain, routing, or ADC enable
settings.

The correct assignment for the I2S right channel is slot 32 (0x20),
"right slot 0", which is the first slot in the FSYNC-low half.

Write ASI_CH2 = 0x20 inside set_dai_fmt() for both SND_SOC_DAIFMT_I2S
and SND_SOC_DAIFMT_LEFT_J (which uses the same FSYNC-based left/right
split).  DSP_A and DSP_B are sequential-slot modes and retain the default
slot 1 assignment.

---
 sound/soc/codecs/tlv320adcx140.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

--- a/tlv320adcx140.c
+++ b/tlv320adcx140.c
@@ -788,9 +788,21 @@
 	switch (fmt & SND_SOC_DAIFMT_FORMAT_MASK) {
 	case SND_SOC_DAIFMT_I2S:
 		iface_reg1 |= ADCX140_I2S_MODE_BIT;
+		/*
+		 * In I2S mode the FSYNC polarity splits the frame into left
+		 * (FSYNC high) and right (FSYNC low) halves.  The POR value
+		 * for ASI_CH2 is 0x01 (left slot 1) which sits outside the
+		 * FSYNC-high window for a standard stereo frame, so the ADC
+		 * never drives that slot.  Slot 32 (0x20) is right slot 0
+		 * -- the first slot in the FSYNC-low half -- the correct
+		 * position for the second stereo channel.
+		 */
+		snd_soc_component_write(component, ADCX140_ASI_CH2, 0x20);
 		break;
 	case SND_SOC_DAIFMT_LEFT_J:
 		iface_reg1 |= ADCX140_LEFT_JUST_BIT;
+		/* Same left/right FSYNC split as I2S; CH2 must use right slot 0 */
+		snd_soc_component_write(component, ADCX140_ASI_CH2, 0x20);
 		break;
 	case SND_SOC_DAIFMT_DSP_A:
 		offset = 1;
